      "acceptanceCriteria": "The choice of turbulence model, hemolysis damage model form, and blood rheology constitutive law must be justified with supporting literature and sensitivity analysis at Gradation 5.",
      "rationale": "Model form uncertainty is the dominant epistemic gap. The power-law hemolysis damage model was selected without documented sensitivity analysis comparing alternative model forms. Turbulence model selection is not justified for the transitional flow regime present in the VAD."
